{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1190,"text":"For as long as I can remember,"},{"time":3190,"text":"I have felt a very deep connection\nto animals and to the ocean."},{"time":7809,"text":"And at this age, my personal idol\nwas Flipper the dolphin."},{"time":13266,"text":"And when I first learned\nabout endangered species,"},{"time":16133,"text":"I was truly distressed to know\nthat every day,"},{"time":19847,"text":"animals were being wiped\noff the face of this Earth forever."},{"time":23395,"text":"And I wanted to do something to help,\nbut I always wondered:"},{"time":26426,"text":"What could one person possibly do\nto make a difference?"},{"time":30282,"text":"And it would be 30 years,"},{"time":32317,"text":"but I would eventually get\nthe answer to that question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36129,"text":"When these heartbreaking\nimages of oiled birds"},{"time":39295,"text":"finally began to emerge\nfrom the Gulf of Mexico last year"},{"time":42397,"text":"during the horrific BP oil spill,"},{"time":44746,"text":"a German biologist by the name\nof Silvia Gaus was quoted as saying,"},{"time":48854,"text":"\"We should just euthanize all oiled birds,"},{"time":51562,"text":"because studies have shown"},{"time":52886,"text":"that fewer than one percent of them\nsurvive after being released.\""},{"time":57882,"text":"And I could not disagree more."},{"time":60438,"text":"In addition,"},{"time":61749,"text":"I believe that every oiled animal\ndeserves a second chance at life."},{"time":65724,"text":"And I want to tell you why\nI feel so strongly about this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69204,"text":"On June 23, 2000,"},{"time":71261,"text":"a ship named the Treasure sank\noff the coast of Cape Town, South Africa,"},{"time":75175,"text":"spilling 1,300 tons of fuel,"},{"time":77587,"text":"which polluted the habitats\nof nearly half the entire world population"},{"time":83047,"text":"of African penguins."},{"time":85084,"text":"Now, the ship sank\nbetween Robben Island to the south,"},{"time":88217,"text":"and Dassen Island to the north --"},{"time":90591,"text":"two of the penguins' main\nbreeding islands."},{"time":93000,"text":"And exactly six years\nand three days earlier,"},{"time":97044,"text":"on June 20, 1994,"},{"time":99790,"text":"a ship named the Apollo Sea\nsank near Dassen Island,"},{"time":102710,"text":"oiling 10,000 penguins,\nhalf of which died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107254,"text":"Now when the Treasure sank in 2000,"},{"time":109075,"text":"it was the height\nof the best breeding season"},{"time":112000,"text":"scientists had ever recorded\nfor the African penguin,"},{"time":115918,"text":"which at the time, was listed\nas a threatened species."},{"time":118909,"text":"And soon, nearly 20,000 penguins"},{"time":121667,"text":"were covered with this toxic oil."},{"time":124102,"text":"The local seabird rescue\ncenter, named SANCCOB,"},{"time":127183,"text":"immediately launched\na massive rescue operation,"},{"time":130259,"text":"and this soon would become\nthe largest animal rescue ever undertaken."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135215,"text":"At the time, I was working\ndown the street."},{"time":137302,"text":"I was a penguin aquarist\nat the New England Aquarium."},{"time":140128,"text":"And exactly 11 years ago yesterday,"},{"time":144212,"text":"the phone rang in the penguin office."},{"time":146641,"text":"And with that call,\nmy life would change forever."},{"time":149609,"text":"It was Estelle van Der Merwe\ncalling from SANCCOB,"},{"time":152233,"text":"saying, \"Please come help."},{"time":154094,"text":"We have thousands of oiled penguins"},{"time":156824,"text":"and thousands of willing\nbut completely inexperienced volunteers."},{"time":162239,"text":"And we need penguin experts\nto come train and supervise them.\""},{"time":165866,"text":"So two days later,"},{"time":167374,"text":"I was on a plane headed for Cape Town"},{"time":169369,"text":"with a team of penguin specialists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172227,"text":"And the scene inside of this building\nwas devastating and surreal."},{"time":177152,"text":"In fact, many people\ncompared it to a war zone."},{"time":180573,"text":"Last week, a 10-year-old girl asked me:"},{"time":183734,"text":"\"What did it feel like\nwhen you first walked into that building"},{"time":187534,"text":"and saw so many oiled penguins?\""},{"time":191722,"text":"And this is what happened."},{"time":193116,"text":"I was instantly transported\nback to that moment in time."},{"time":197862,"text":"Penguins are very vocal birds\nand really, really noisy,"},{"time":201854,"text":"so I expected to walk into this building"},{"time":204375,"text":"and be met with this cacophony\nof honking and braying and squawking."},{"time":208351,"text":"But instead,"},{"time":209829,"text":"when we stepped through\nthose doors and into the building,"},{"time":213635,"text":"it was eerily silent."},{"time":217306,"text":"So it was very clear"},{"time":218783,"text":"these were stressed,\nsick, traumatized birds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222808,"text":"The other thing that was so striking"},{"time":225171,"text":"was the sheer number of volunteers."},{"time":228123,"text":"Up to 1,000 people a day\ncame to the rescue center."},{"time":231837,"text":"Eventually, over the course\nof this rescue,"},{"time":234000,"text":"more than 12-and-a-half\nthousand volunteers"},{"time":237453,"text":"came from all over the world to Cape Town,"},{"time":239796,"text":"to help save these birds."},{"time":241399,"text":"And the amazing thing\nwas that not one of them had to be there."},{"time":246018,"text":"Yet they were."},{"time":247193,"text":"So for the few of us that were there\nin a professional capacity,"},{"time":250522,"text":"this extraordinary volunteer response\nto this animal crisis"},{"time":254000,"text":"was profoundly moving and awe-inspiring."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257522,"text":"So the day after we arrived,"},{"time":258903,"text":"two of us from the aquarium\nwere put in charge of room two."},{"time":261832,"text":"Room two had more\nthan 4,000 oiled penguins in it."},{"time":266055,"text":"Now, mind you --"},{"time":267230,"text":"three days earlier,\nwe had 60 penguins under our care,"},{"time":270547,"text":"so we were definitely overwhelmed"},{"time":272884,"text":"and just a bit terrified --\nat least I was."},{"time":275832,"text":"Personally, I really didn't know"},{"time":277857,"text":"if I was capable of handling\nsuch a monstrous task."},{"time":282258,"text":"And collectively,"},{"time":283591,"text":"we really didn't know\nif we could pull this off."},{"time":286592,"text":"Because we all knew\nthat just six years earlier,"},{"time":289898,"text":"half as many penguins\nhad been oiled and rescued,"},{"time":292937,"text":"and only half of them had survived."},{"time":295889,"text":"So would it be humanly possible\nto save this many oiled penguins?"},{"time":300129,"text":"We just did not know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302481,"text":"But what gave us hope"},{"time":303804,"text":"were these incredibly dedicated\nand brave volunteers,"},{"time":307223,"text":"three of whom here\nare force-feeding penguins."},{"time":310090,"text":"You may notice they're wearing\nvery thick gloves."},{"time":312638,"text":"And what you should know\nabout African penguins"},{"time":315153,"text":"is that they have razor-sharp beaks."},{"time":318105,"text":"And before long,"},{"time":319303,"text":"our bodies were covered head to toe"},{"time":322160,"text":"with these nasty wounds\ninflicted by the terrified penguins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326150,"text":"Now the day after we arrived,\na new crisis began to unfold."},{"time":329739,"text":"The oil slick was now moving\nnorth towards Dassen Island,"},{"time":332966,"text":"and the rescuers despaired,"},{"time":335259,"text":"because they knew if the oil hit,"},{"time":337418,"text":"it would not be possible\nto rescue any more oiled birds."},{"time":340291,"text":"And there really were no good solutions."},{"time":342299,"text":"But then finally,"},{"time":343474,"text":"one of the researchers\nthrew out this crazy idea."},{"time":346443,"text":"He said, \"OK, why don't we try\nand collect the birds"},{"time":350093,"text":"at the greatest risk of getting oiled\" --"},{"time":352092,"text":"they collected 20,000 --"},{"time":353859,"text":"\"and we'll ship them 500 miles\nup the coast to Port Elizabeth"},{"time":358490,"text":"in these open-air trucks,"},{"time":359817,"text":"and release them\ninto the clean waters there"},{"time":362024,"text":"and let them swim back home?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":364056,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":368145,"text":"So three of those penguins --\nPeter, Pamela and Percy --"},{"time":371487,"text":"wore satellite tags,"},{"time":372662,"text":"and the researchers crossed their fingers"},{"time":374665,"text":"and hoped that by the time\nthey got back home,"},{"time":376930,"text":"the oil would be cleaned up\nfrom their islands."},{"time":379179,"text":"And luckily, the day they arrived, it was."},{"time":382124,"text":"So it had been a huge gamble,\nbut it had paid off."},{"time":386067,"text":"And so they know now\nthat they can use this strategy"},{"time":389001,"text":"in future oil spills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"So in wildlife rescue as in life,"},{"time":394378,"text":"we learn from each previous experience,"},{"time":396544,"text":"and we learn from both\nour successes and our failures."},{"time":400774,"text":"And the main thing learned\nduring the Apollo Sea rescue in '94"},{"time":405203,"text":"was that most of those penguins\nhad died due to the unwitting use"},{"time":409606,"text":"of poorly ventilated\ntransport boxes and trucks,"},{"time":412922,"text":"because they just had not been prepared"},{"time":414848,"text":"to deal with so many\noiled penguins at once."},{"time":417189,"text":"So in these six years\nbetween these two oil spills,"},{"time":420127,"text":"they've built thousands\nof these well-ventilated boxes."},{"time":423484,"text":"And as a result,\nduring the Treasure rescue,"},{"time":426381,"text":"just 160 penguins died\nduring the transport process,"},{"time":431000,"text":"as opposed to 5,000."},{"time":433001,"text":"So this alone was a huge victory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435760,"text":"Something else learned\nduring the Apollo rescue"},{"time":438019,"text":"was how to train the penguins"},{"time":439539,"text":"to take fish freely from their hands,"},{"time":442540,"text":"using these training boxes."},{"time":444503,"text":"And we used this technique again\nduring the Treasure rescue."},{"time":448000,"text":"But an interesting thing was noted\nduring the training process."},{"time":452734,"text":"The first penguins to make\nthat transition to free feeding"},{"time":456216,"text":"were the ones that had\na metal band on their wing"},{"time":459180,"text":"from the Apollo Sea spill\nsix years earlier."},{"time":462633,"text":"So penguins learn\nfrom previous experience, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466902,"text":"So all of those penguins had to have\nthe oil meticulously cleaned"},{"time":470678,"text":"from their bodies."},{"time":471860,"text":"It would take two people at least an hour\njust to clean one penguin."},{"time":476687,"text":"When you clean a penguin,"},{"time":478000,"text":"you first have to spray it\nwith a degreaser."},{"time":480230,"text":"And this brings me to my favorite story\nfrom the Treasure rescue."},{"time":484276,"text":"About a year prior to this oil spill,"},{"time":486891,"text":"a 17-year-old student\nhad invented a degreaser."},{"time":490669,"text":"And they'd been using it\nat SANCCOB with great success,"},{"time":493510,"text":"so they began using it\nduring the Treasure rescue."},{"time":496183,"text":"But partway through, they ran out."},{"time":499571,"text":"So in a panic, Estelle\nfrom SANCCOB called the student"},{"time":502472,"text":"and said, \"Please, you have to make more!\""},{"time":504532,"text":"So he raced to the lab"},{"time":505809,"text":"and made enough to clean\nthe rest of the birds."},{"time":508911,"text":"So I just think it is the coolest thing"},{"time":511719,"text":"that a teenager invented a product"},{"time":515281,"text":"that helped save the lives\nof thousands of animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519297,"text":"So what happened\nto those 20,000 oiled penguins?"},{"time":522829,"text":"And was Silvia Gaus right?"},{"time":524866,"text":"Should we routinely euthanize\nall oiled birds"},{"time":528286,"text":"because most of them\nare going to die anyway?"},{"time":530542,"text":"Well, she could not be more wrong."},{"time":533653,"text":"After half a million hours\nof grueling volunteer labor,"},{"time":538000,"text":"more than 90 percent\nof those oiled penguins"},{"time":540407,"text":"were successfully returned to the wild."},{"time":543415,"text":"And we know from follow-up studies"},{"time":545629,"text":"that they have lived just as long\nas never-oiled penguins,"},{"time":549760,"text":"and bred nearly as successfully."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552482,"text":"And in addition,"},{"time":553657,"text":"about 3,000 penguin chicks\nwere rescued and hand raised."},{"time":557510,"text":"And again, we know\nfrom long-term monitoring"},{"time":560203,"text":"that more of these hand-raised chicks\nsurvive to adulthood and breeding age"},{"time":566115,"text":"than do parent-raised chicks."},{"time":568234,"text":"Armed with this knowledge,\nSANCCOB has a chick-bolstering project,"},{"time":571714,"text":"and every year, they rescue\nand raise abandoned chicks,"},{"time":574714,"text":"and they have a very impressive,\n80 percent success rate."},{"time":579262,"text":"This is critically important,"},{"time":581146,"text":"because one year ago,"},{"time":583598,"text":"the African penguin\nwas declared endangered."},{"time":586948,"text":"And they could be extinct\nin less than 10 years"},{"time":590778,"text":"if we don't do something\nnow to protect them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593683,"text":"So what did I learn"},{"time":595000,"text":"from this intense\nand unforgettable experience?"},{"time":598204,"text":"Personally, I learned that I am capable\nof handling so much more"},{"time":601792,"text":"than I ever dreamed possible."},{"time":603552,"text":"And I learned that one person\ncan make a huge difference."},{"time":607485,"text":"Just look at that 17-year-old."},{"time":609517,"text":"And when we come together and work as one,"},{"time":613168,"text":"we can achieve extraordinary things."},{"time":615966,"text":"And truly, to be a part of something\nso much larger than yourself"},{"time":619966,"text":"is the most rewarding experience\nyou can possibly have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624603,"text":"So I'd like to leave you\nwith one final thought"},{"time":627015,"text":"and a challenge, if you will."},{"time":628612,"text":"My mission as The Penguin Lady\nis to raise awareness and funding"},{"time":632827,"text":"to protect penguins."},{"time":634779,"text":"But why should any of you\ncare about penguins?"},{"time":637270,"text":"Well, you should care\nbecause they're an indicator species."},{"time":641000,"text":"And simply put: if penguins are dying,\nit means our oceans are dying."},{"time":645905,"text":"And we ultimately will be affected,"},{"time":647945,"text":"because, as Sylvia Earle says,"},{"time":650110,"text":"\"The oceans are our life-support system.\""},{"time":653000,"text":"And the two main threats to penguins today"},{"time":655500,"text":"are overfishing and global warming."},{"time":658130,"text":"And these are two things"},{"time":659314,"text":"that each one of us actually has\nthe power to do something about."},{"time":664012,"text":"So if we each do our part, together,\nwe can make a difference,"},{"time":668193,"text":"and we can help keep\npenguins from going extinct."},{"time":671622,"text":"Humans have always been the greatest\nthreat to penguins,"},{"time":675072,"text":"but we are now their only hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677191,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678366,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}